snippet.title: Kids visiting outdoor play area and having fun Tokyo's best open area, fun video fro kids,funvideo
snippet.description:
Kasai Rinkai Park (葛西臨海公園 Kasai Rinkai Kōen) is a park in Edogawa, Tokyo, Japan, which officially opened on June 1, 1989.[2] The park includes a bird sanctuary and the Tokyo Sea Life Park aquarium. It was built on reclaimed land which includes two manmade islands, a observation deck and a hotel. It is the second-largest park in the 23 wards of Tokyo (after Mizumoto Park).[3]

The 117-metre (384 ft) tall Diamond and Flower Ferris Wheel opened at the park in 2001.[3] On a clear day, it affords views of Tokyo Bay, Chiba, Edogawa, Tokyo Disneyland, and Mount Fuji. It is reportedly the second tallest ferris wheel in Japan.[4]

About a third of the park is designated a sea bird sanctuary, which houses a Sea Bird Centre that provides information on the local bird species.[4] The park also has two beaches on artificial islands. The west island is connected to land by the Kasai Nagisa bridge and is a popular place for recreation.[2] The east island is closed to the public as a protected bird habitat and Ramsar site since 2018.[1]

The park is always crowded during the 'hanami' period of spring, when the Japanese party under cherry trees in bloom.

Another great day at Drusillas Park. This time with Emma’s cousins Charlie and Jessica. No animals again this time. In another video one day I am sure.

Love this place. Its a great. Went on the new train that has replaced the Thomas Train. The Safari Express. You can see the similarities in the video. Still two rides to open in the next few weeks. Hippopotobus and the Flying Cheetahs. 

Also went on the Hello Kitty Rides as well as some of the outdoor play area.
